## PROMISSORY AND SUPERLATIVE LEXICON

HIGH-CONFIDENCE triggers (confidence ≥ 0.90) — flag when used as a product, firm, or outcome claim:

Absolute performance / capital claims:
"guaranteed", "capital guaranteed", "capital protected" (unless legally verified),
"risk-free", "no risk", "zero risk", "certain return", "assured return"

Superiority / ranking claims:
"best", "best-in-class", "top-performing", "number one", "#1", "market-leading",
"unrivalled", "unmatched", "second to none", "industry-leading", "world-class",
"market-beating", "outperforms the market"

Promissory future language:
"will deliver", "will achieve", "will outperform", "will generate", "will provide"

Unqualified superlatives:
"exceptional returns", "outstanding performance", "superior results",
"unparalleled", "extraordinary", "unprecedented performance"

BORDERLINE TERMS (confidence 0.71–0.85 — flag only when used as a superiority or outcome claim, not as scope description):
"comprehensive", "robust", "proven", "established", "consistent", "strong",
"solid", "resilient", "diversified" (when used as a performance claim)

SAFE HARBOUR — Do NOT flag:
"aims to", "seeks to", "targets", "has historically demonstrated", "may",
"past performance is not a reliable indicator of future results",
"the value of investments may go down as well as up",
"for professional investors only", "subject to market conditions",
"in accordance with applicable law"

